\cosh\left(\frac{\pi}{2}\right)=\frac{1}{2}e^{-{\pi/2}}(1+e^\pi)
\cosh\left(\frac{\pi}{2}\right)=\cos\left(i\frac{\pi}{2}\right)
=Re\{e^{i.i\frac{\pi}{2}}\}
=Re\{e^{-\frac{\pi}{2}}\}
e^{-\frac{\pi}{2}}
\frac{e^{-\frac{\pi}{2}}+e^{\frac{\pi}{2}}}{2}
\cosh(x)
\frac{e^{x} + e^{-x}}{2}
\cosh\left(\frac{\pi}{2}\right)=\frac{e^{\frac{\pi}{2}} + e^{-\frac{\pi}{2}}}{2} = \frac{1}{2}e^{-\frac{\pi}{2}}(1 + e^x)
\left(1+\frac1{1^2}\right)\left(1+\frac1{3^2}\right)\left(1+\frac1{5^2}\right)\left(1+\frac1{7^2}\right)\dotsm= \cosh \frac\pi 2
